## 3. Palindrome Problems — DP

### 3.1 Longest Palindromic Subsequence

```java
// LPS(s) = LCS(s, reverse(s))
// Or directly:

// Time: O(n²) | Space: O(n²)
public static int longestPalindromicSubsequence(String s) {
    int n = s.length();
    int[][] dp = new int[n][n];

    // Every single char is palindrome of length 1
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) dp[i][i] = 1;

    // Fill for increasing lengths
    for (int len = 2; len <= n; len++) {
        for (int i = 0; i <= n - len; i++) {
            int j = i + len - 1;
            if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(j)) {
                dp[i][j] = 2 + (len == 2 ? 0 : dp[i + 1][j - 1]);
            } else {
                dp[i][j] = Math.max(dp[i + 1][j], dp[i][j - 1]);
            }
        }
    }
    return dp[0][n - 1];
}
```

### 3.2 Minimum Insertions to Make Palindrome

```java
// Min insertions = n - LPS(s)
public static int minInsertions(String s) {
    return s.length() - longestPalindromicSubsequence(s);
}
```

### 3.3 Count Palindromic Substrings (DP)

```java
// Time: O(n²) | Space: O(n²)
public static int countPalindromes(String s) {
    int n = s.length(), count = 0;
    boolean[][] dp = new boolean[n][n];

    // All single chars
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { dp[i][i] = true; count++; }

    // All pairs
    for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
        if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(i + 1)) {
            dp[i][i + 1] = true;
            count++;
        }
    }

    // Length 3+
    for (int len = 3; len <= n; len++) {
        for (int i = 0; i <= n - len; i++) {
            int j = i + len - 1;
            if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(j) && dp[i + 1][j - 1]) {
                dp[i][j] = true;
                count++;
            }
        }
    }
    return count;
}
```

### 3.4 Palindrome Partitioning — Minimum Cuts (DP)

```java
// Minimum cuts to partition string into all palindromes
// Time: O(n²) | Space: O(n²)
public static int minCut(String s) {
    int n = s.length();
    boolean[][] isPalin = new boolean[n][n];

    // Precompute palindrome table
    for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {
            isPalin[i][j] = s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(j)
                && (j - i <= 2 || isPalin[i + 1][j - 1]);
        }
    }

    // dp[i] = min cuts for s[0..i]
    int[] dp = new int[n];
    Arrays.fill(dp, Integer.MAX_VALUE);

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (isPalin[0][i]) {
            dp[i] = 0;
        } else {
            for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
                if (isPalin[j][i] && dp[j - 1] != Integer.MAX_VALUE) {
                    dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[j - 1] + 1);
                }
            }
        }
    }
    return dp[n - 1];
}
```

### 3.5 Palindrome Check with Recursion + Memo:
```java
// dp[i][j] = is s[i..j] a palindrome?
private static int[][] palMemo;

public static boolean isPalindrome(String s, int i, int j) {
    if (i >= j) return true;
    if (palMemo[i][j] != -1) return palMemo[i][j] == 1;

    boolean result = s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(j) && isPalindrome(s, i+1, j-1);
    palMemo[i][j] = result ? 1 : 0;
    return result;
}
```

