## 5. Distinct Subsequences

Count distinct occurrences of t as a subsequence of s.

```java
// s = "rabbbit", t = "rabbit" → 3
// Time: O(m*n) | Space: O(m*n)
public static int numDistinct(String s, String t) {
    int m = s.length(), n = t.length();
    long[][] dp = new long[m + 1][n + 1];

    for (int i = 0; i <= m; i++) dp[i][0] = 1; // empty t always matches

    for (int i = 1; i <= m; i++) {
        for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++) {
            dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j]; // skip s[i]
            if (s.charAt(i - 1) == t.charAt(j - 1)) {
                dp[i][j] += dp[i - 1][j - 1]; // use s[i]
            }
        }
    }
    return (int) dp[m][n];
}
```

