## 6. Wildcard Pattern Matching

`?` matches any single char. `*` matches any sequence (including empty).

```java
// Time: O(m*n) | Space: O(m*n)
public static boolean isMatch(String s, String p) {
    int m = s.length(), n = p.length();
    boolean[][] dp = new boolean[m + 1][n + 1];
    dp[0][0] = true;

    // Pattern of only '*' can match empty string
    for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++) {
        if (p.charAt(j - 1) == '*') dp[0][j] = dp[0][j - 1];
    }

    for (int i = 1; i <= m; i++) {
        for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++) {
            char pc = p.charAt(j - 1);
            if (pc == '*') {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j] || dp[i][j - 1];
                // dp[i-1][j]: * matches one char of s
                // dp[i][j-1]: * matches empty
            } else if (pc == '?' || s.charAt(i - 1) == pc) {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1];
            }
        }
    }
    return dp[m][n];
}
```

