## 7. String Comparison Techniques

### Lexicographic Comparison:
```java
// compareTo: char by char, returns difference at first mismatch
"apple".compareTo("application"); // 'e' - 'i' = -4 (negative → apple < application)

// Custom comparator for sorting
String[] words = {"banana", "apple", "cherry"};
Arrays.sort(words);                          // lexicographic
Arrays.sort(words, (a, b) -> b.compareTo(a)); // reverse
Arrays.sort(words, Comparator.comparingInt(String::length)); // by length
```

### Moving Index for Comparison:
```java
// Compare two strings starting from different indices
public static boolean compareFrom(String s1, int i, String s2, int j, int len) {
    for (int k = 0; k < len; k++) {
        if (i + k >= s1.length() || j + k >= s2.length()) return false;
        if (s1.charAt(i + k) != s2.charAt(j + k)) return false;
    }
    return true;
}

// Sliding comparison for pattern detection
public static boolean contains(String text, String pattern) {
    int n = text.length(), m = pattern.length();
    for (int i = 0; i <= n - m; i++) {
        if (compareFrom(text, i, pattern, 0, m)) return true;
    }
    return false;
}
```

