## 8. Index Movement Patterns in Strings

### Two Pointer:
```java
// Inward movement — palindrome check
int l = 0, r = s.length() - 1;
while (l < r) {
    if (s.charAt(l) != s.charAt(r)) return false;
    l++; r--;
}

// One pointer forward, one backward — reverse
while (l < r) {
    char temp = arr[l];
    arr[l++] = arr[r];
    arr[r--] = temp;
}
```

### Sliding Window:
```java
// Fixed-size window of size k
int[] freq = new int[26];
for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) freq[s.charAt(i) - 'a']++;

for (int i = k; i < s.length(); i++) {
    freq[s.charAt(i) - 'a']++;       // add new char
    freq[s.charAt(i - k) - 'a']--;   // remove old char
    // process window
}
```

### Fast and Slow Pointer (Cycle Detection in Strings):
```java
// Find pattern start
int slow = 0, fast = 0;
while (fast < n && condition) {
    fast++;
    if (anotherCondition) slow++;
}
```

### Skip Pointer (Jump Indices):
```java
// Used in KMP — skip already matched characters
int[] lps = computeLPS(pattern);
int i = 0, j = 0; // i for text, j for pattern
while (i < text.length()) {
    if (text.charAt(i) == pattern.charAt(j)) {
        i++; j++;
    }
    if (j == pattern.length()) {
        // found match
        j = lps[j - 1]; // jump using LPS table
    } else if (i < text.length() && text.charAt(i) != pattern.charAt(j)) {
        if (j != 0) j = lps[j - 1]; // skip ahead
        else i++;
    }
}
```

