## 10. Z Algorithm — Pattern Matching

Z-array: `Z[i]` = length of longest substring starting at `i` that matches prefix of string.

```java
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(n)
public static int[] zFunction(String s) {
    int n = s.length();
    int[] Z = new int[n];
    int l = 0, r = 0;

    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        if (i < r) Z[i] = Math.min(r - i, Z[i - l]);

        while (i + Z[i] < n && s.charAt(Z[i]) == s.charAt(i + Z[i])) {
            Z[i]++;
        }
        if (i + Z[i] > r) { l = i; r = i + Z[i]; }
    }
    return Z;
}

// Pattern search using Z
public static List<Integer> searchZ(String text, String pattern) {
    String concat = pattern + "$" + text;
    int[] Z = zFunction(concat);
    List<Integer> matches = new ArrayList<>();
    int m = pattern.length();

    for (int i = m + 1; i < concat.length(); i++) {
        if (Z[i] == m) matches.add(i - m - 1);
    }
    return matches;
}
```

