## 12. Rabin-Karp — Rolling Hash

Pattern matching using hashing — avoids char-by-char comparison in most cases.

```java
// Time: O(n+m) average, O(n*m) worst | Space: O(1)
public static List<Integer> rabinKarp(String text, String pattern) {
    int n = text.length(), m = pattern.length();
    int base = 26, mod = 1_000_000_007;
    List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();

    long patHash = 0, winHash = 0, power = 1;

    // Compute base^(m-1) % mod
    for (int i = 0; i < m - 1; i++) power = power * base % mod;

    // Initial hashes
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        patHash = (patHash * base + pattern.charAt(i)) % mod;
        winHash = (winHash * base + text.charAt(i)) % mod;
    }

    for (int i = 0; i <= n - m; i++) {
        if (winHash == patHash) {
            // Verify (avoid hash collision)
            if (text.substring(i, i + m).equals(pattern)) {
                result.add(i);
            }
        }
        if (i < n - m) {
            // Roll hash: remove leftmost, add new rightmost
            winHash = (winHash - text.charAt(i) * power % mod + mod) % mod;
            winHash = (winHash * base + text.charAt(i + m)) % mod;
        }
    }
    return result;
}
```

