## 13. Minimum Window Substring

Find smallest window in s that contains all chars of t.

```java
// Time: O(n) | Space: O(k)
public static String minWindow(String s, String t) {
    if (s.isEmpty() || t.isEmpty()) return "";

    int[] need = new int[128];
    for (char c : t.toCharArray()) need[c]++;

    int left = 0, right = 0;
    int formed = 0, required = (int) t.chars().distinct().count();
    int[] window = new int[128];

    int minLen = Integer.MAX_VALUE, minLeft = 0;

    while (right < s.length()) {
        char c = s.charAt(right++);
        window[c]++;
        if (need[c] > 0 && window[c] == need[c]) formed++;

        while (formed == required) {
            if (right - left < minLen) {
                minLen = right - left;
                minLeft = left;
            }
            char lc = s.charAt(left++);
            window[lc]--;
            if (need[lc] > 0 && window[lc] < need[lc]) formed--;
        }
    }
    return minLen == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? "" : s.substring(minLeft, minLeft + minLen);
}
```

