## 16. Word Break Problem (DP)

Can string s be segmented into words from dictionary?

```java
// Time: O(n²) | Space: O(n)
public static boolean wordBreak(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
    Set<String> dict = new HashSet<>(wordDict);
    int n = s.length();
    boolean[] dp = new boolean[n + 1];
    dp[0] = true;

    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
            if (dp[j] && dict.contains(s.substring(j, i))) {
                dp[i] = true;
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    return dp[n];
}

// Return all valid sentences
public static List<String> wordBreakAll(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
    Set<String> dict = new HashSet<>(wordDict);
    Map<Integer, List<String>> memo = new HashMap<>();
    return helper(s, 0, dict, memo);
}

private static List<String> helper(String s, int start,
                                    Set<String> dict, Map<Integer, List<String>> memo) {
    if (memo.containsKey(start)) return memo.get(start);
    List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
    if (start == s.length()) { result.add(""); return result; }

    for (int end = start + 1; end <= s.length(); end++) {
        String word = s.substring(start, end);
        if (dict.contains(word)) {
            for (String rest : helper(s, end, dict, memo)) {
                result.add(word + (rest.isEmpty() ? "" : " " + rest));
            }
        }
    }
    memo.put(start, result);
    return result;
}
```

